# Three scripted decisions for the smoke fixture. The Mandate caps the loop
# at step_cap = 1, so the agent retires cleanly after this one cycle (three steps) executes.
#
# Step 1 (cycle 0): invoke the echo tool. Produces an evidence record on disk at
# evidence/<slug(claim_seed)>-<first 8 hex of EvidenceId>.json — here
# evidence/seed-1-1d6a153a.json (slug "seed-1"; EvidenceId =
# sha256(canonical_json({"args":{"hello":"smoke"},"result":{"echoed":{"hello":"smoke"}},"tool":"echo"}))
# = 1d6a153a...). Recompute the suffix with `EvidenceId::new(...)` and the path
# with `coral_node::fs::evidence_relpath("seed-1", &id)` if the canonical-JSON
# rules in src/evidence.rs ever change.
{"type":"call_tools","calls":[{"name":"echo","args":{"hello":"smoke"},"claim_seed":"seed-1"}]}
# Step 2 (cycle 0): write the canonical output citing that evidence path.
{"type":"write_output","body":"smoke test passed","citations":["evidence/seed-1-1d6a153a.json"]}
# Step 3 (cycle 0): idle. The loop's step_cap=1 cap ends the cycle; the step_cap (1) retires the agent.
{"type":"idle","next_after":50}
